In article <strnlghtCvB6EM.Bpn@netcom.com> strnlght@netcom.com (David Sternlight) writes:
> In article <9408281626.AA00152@flevel.demon.co.uk>,
> David Southwell <david@flevel.demon.co.uk> wrote:
> >Let us say someone was asked to prepare an analysis in response to the
> >questions "How safe is RSA"
> >
> >
> >Under what sub headings do you think the analysis  should be made?
> 
> An interesting point. I note with some amusement that many who post
> "expert-seeming" replies tend to post analytically devoid statements of the
> form of an "is" in which the analysis, much less the conclusions, are
> essentially left to the reader.
> 
> They seem, at best, to be answers to the question "how would I go about
> analyzing how safe RSA is?", rather than the question that was asked.
> 
> As near as I can make out, such replies come from several possible sources:
> 
> 1. Laziness;
> 2. Ignorance;
> 3. Arrogance;
> 4. That the question, as posed, is unanswerable.
> 
> If the correct answer is (4), writers should say so rather than posting a
> farrago of mathematics, and be willing to take the risk that someone else
> might actually answer the question. Even more helpful would be a response
> (if the writer believes (4) is the correct answer), of the form 'tell me
> what your assumptions are about computer technology and the degree of
> parallel processing and I can give you a better answer'.
> 
> Most helpful of all are answers in which the expert makes the assumptions,
> states what they are, and then gives a result in terms consistent with the
> question rather than consistent with THEIR internal mode of thinking. Thus:
> 'if a, and b, and c, then it will take 3x10**8 years to crack the message,
> but note that there is reason to believe that the NSA (for example) is
> not-a though most commercial adversaries would be'.

I agree. No one has so far responded. Is anyone prepared to have a go?
Repeated question:

Let us say someone was asked to prepare an analysis in response to the
questions "How safe is RSA"


Under what sub headings do you think the analysis  should be made?


